        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When a new request object is instantiate (with no parameter ) in the dispatch method in Zend_Controller_Front ( line 397 $request = new Zend_Controller_Request_Http() ) setRequestUri() is never call in Zend_Http_Request (line 66)\n\nThen $request->getPathInfo() return nothing in Zend_Controller_Router (line 112)\n\nThen no match is fond for controller\/action\n\nThen we end up on default controller\/action\n\nI put a else statment in Zend_Http_Request  with $this->setRequestUri(); and it work for me\n\n{code}\n    public function __construct($uri = null)\n    {\n        if (null !== $uri) {\n            if (!$uri instanceof Zend_Uri) {\n                $uri = Zend_Uri::factory($uri);\n            } \n            if ($uri->valid()) {\n                $path  = $uri->getPath();\n                $query = $uri->getQuery();\n                if (!empty($query)) {\n                    $path .= '?' . $query;\n                }\n\n                $this->setRequestUri($path);\n            }\n        } else {\n\t\t    $this->setRequestUri();\n\t\t}\n    }\n{code}"
        },
